title: COL2_011853
treatment_protocol_ch1: Tissue samples were collected on fresh surgical specimens by pathologists within one hour after surgery from patients who underwent curative colonic resection, then flash frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at -80°C until nucleic acids extraction.
extract_protocol_ch1: Enriched tumor zones were selected from frozen material on HE-stained cryosections to ensure a 60% minimum of tumor cells. Nucleic acids were extracted using QIAamp and RNeasy kits (Qiagen, Courtaboeuf France) according to the manufacturer's instructions. Quantification of samples was done with a NanoDrop ND-1000 spectrophotometer (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Illkirch France). RNA integrity was controlled on an Agilent Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Massy France).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol
hyb_protocol: Expression profiles were established with Affymetrix U133 Plus 2.0 human oligonucleotide microarrays
scan_protocol: Scanning was done with an Affymetrix GeneArray scanner and quantification with the Affymetrix GeneChip Operating Software (Affymetrix, Paris France).
description: gene expression data from stage II primary colon adenocarcinoma after surgery only
data_processing: CEL files were processed in the R/Bioconductor environment. Pre-processing steps (background adjustment, normalization and summarization) were performed with the GCRMA package
data_processing.1: Expression measures were handled on log2 scale for statistical computations as well as for display purposes. Genes with overall low intensity were removed from further analysis. All remaining genes had an expression value greater than log2 (100) in at least 10% of the samples. As tumor samples and/or RNA samples were provided by 4 different centres, genes were then median-centred within each centre individually.
contact_department: Centre de Recherches en Cancérologie de Marseille

treatment_protocol_ch1: Tissue samples were collected on fresh surgical specimens by pathologists within one hour after surgery from patients who underwent curative colonic resection, then flash frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at -80°C until nucleic acids extraction.
extract_protocol_ch1: Enriched tumor zones were selected from frozen material on HE-stained cryosections to ensure a 60% minimum of tumor cells. Nucleic acids were extracted using QIAamp and RNeasy kits (Qiagen, Courtaboeuf France) according to the manufacturer's instructions. Quantification of samples was done with a NanoDrop ND-1000 spectrophotometer (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Illkirch France). RNA integrity was controlled on an Agilent Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Massy France).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol
hyb_protocol: Expression profiles were established with Affymetrix U133 Plus 2.0 human oligonucleotide microarrays
scan_protocol: Scanning was done with an Affymetrix GeneArray scanner and quantification with the Affymetrix GeneChip Operating Software (Affymetrix, Paris France).
description: gene expression data from stage II primary colon adenocarcinoma after surgery only
data_processing: CEL files were processed in the R/Bioconductor environment. Pre-processing steps (background adjustment, normalization and summarization) were performed with the GCRMA package
data_processing.1: Expression measures were handled on log2 scale for statistical computations as well as for display purposes. Genes with overall low intensity were removed from further analysis. All remaining genes had an expression value greater than log2 (100) in at least 10% of the samples. As tumor samples and/or RNA samples were provided by 4 different centres, genes were then median-centred within each centre individually.
contact_department: Centre de Recherches en Cancérologie de Marseille

description: gene expression data from stage II primary colon adenocarcinoma after surgery only
data_processing: CEL files were processed in the R/Bioconductor environment. Pre-processing steps (background adjustment, normalization and summarization) were performed with the GCRMA package
data_processing.1: Expression measures were handled on log2 scale for statistical computations as well as for display purposes. Genes with overall low intensity were removed from further analysis. All remaining genes had an expression value greater than log2 (100) in at least 10% of the samples. As tumor samples and/or RNA samples were provided by 4 different centres, genes were then median-centred within each centre individually.

title: COL2_720
treatment_protocol_ch1: Tissue samples were collected on fresh surgical specimens by pathologists within one hour after surgery from patients who underwent curative colonic resection, then flash frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at -80°C until nucleic acids extraction.

treatment_protocol_ch1: Tissue samples were collected on fresh surgical specimens by pathologists within one hour after surgery from patients who underwent curative colonic resection, then flash frozen in liquid nitrogen and stored at -80°C until nucleic acids extraction.
extract_protocol_ch1: Enriched tumor zones were selected from frozen material on HE-stained cryosections to ensure a 60% minimum of tumor cells. Nucleic acids were extracted using QIAamp and RNeasy kits (Qiagen, Courtaboeuf France) according to the manufacturer's instructions. Quantification of samples was done with a NanoDrop ND-1000 spectrophotometer (Thermo Fisher Scientific, Illkirch France). RNA integrity was controlled on an Agilent Bioanalyzer (Agilent Technologies, Massy France).
label_protocol_ch1: Biotinylated cRNA were prepared according to the standard Affymetrix protocol
hyb_protocol: Expression profiles were established with Affymetrix U133 Plus 2.0 human oligonucleotide microarrays
scan_protocol: Scanning was done with an Affymetrix GeneArray scanner and quantification with the Affymetrix GeneChip Operating Software (Affymetrix, Paris France).
description: gene expression data from stage II primary colon adenocarcinoma after surgery only
data_processing: CEL files were processed in the R/Bioconductor environment. Pre-processing steps (background adjustment, normalization and summarization) were performed with the GCRMA package
data_processing.1: Expression measures were handled on log2 scale for statistical computations as well as for display purposes. Genes with overall low intensity were removed from further analysis. All remaining genes had an expression value greater than log2 (100) in at least 10% of the samples. As tumor samples and/or RNA samples were provided by 4 different centres, genes were then median-centred within each centre individually.
contact_department: Centre de Recherches en Cancérologie de Marseille
